(Finding #1: [Critical] Minting policy liquidity_mint doesn't validate minted tokens) Tj T*
(  Detector: missing-minting-policy-check) Tj T*
(  Module: liquidity_mint) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/liquidity_mint.ak:21) Tj T*
(Description: Mint handler never accesses the transaction's mint field. An attacker could) Tj T*
(    mint arbitrary token names under this policy.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Check `self.mint` \(or `transaction.mint`\) to validate token names and) Tj T*
(    quantities.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #2: [Critical] Unrestricted minting policy liquidity_mint) Tj T*
(  Detector: unrestricted-minting) Tj T*
(  Module: liquidity_mint) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/liquidity_mint.ak:21) Tj T*
(Description: Mint handler has no authorization checks \(no signatories, inputs, mint, or) Tj T*
(    reference input validation\). Anyone can mint tokens.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Add authorization: check `self.extra_signatories` for an admin key, or) Tj T*
(    verify a specific input UTXO is consumed.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #3: [High] Lower bound time manipulation risk in orders.spend) Tj T*
(  Detector: missing-validity-range) Tj T*
(  Module: orders) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/orders.ak:44) Tj T*
(Description: Handler uses get_lower_bound for time-sensitive logic with field\(s\)) Tj T*
(    [entered_position_time] but never checks the upper bound. An attacker can set the) Tj T*
(    lower bound arbitrarily far in the past, manipulating time-based calculations) Tj T*
(    \(interest accrual, fee computation, deadline checks\).) Tj T*
ET
